  <LegalContent title="Terms of Services" lastUpdated="V1.0 — Last edited 10 January 2022">

    <h2>I. Introduction</h2>
    <p>These Terms of Services ("Agreement") govern your use of AllSafe IT's managed IT services, cybersecurity solutions, and related offerings. By engaging AllSafe IT's services, you agree to be bound by this Agreement. If you do not agree to these terms, please do not use our services.</p>

    <h2>II. Services Provided</h2>
    <p>AllSafe IT provides managed IT services including but not limited to: 24/7 helpdesk support, network monitoring, cybersecurity management, cloud services, IT consulting, and related technology services. The specific services delivered to each client are defined in the applicable Service Order or Statement of Work.</p>
    <p>AllSafe IT reserves the right to modify, suspend, or discontinue any service with reasonable notice to the client. We will use commercially reasonable efforts to minimize disruption to your operations.</p>

    <h2>III. Payment and Fees</h2>
    <p>Services are billed on a monthly basis unless otherwise specified in the Service Order. Payment is due within 30 days of the invoice date. Late payments may incur interest charges at the rate of 1.5% per month.</p>
    <p>AllSafe IT reserves the right to adjust fees with 30 days' written notice. Fees are non-refundable except as expressly set forth in this Agreement or required by applicable law.</p>

    <h2>IV. Data Security and Confidentiality</h2>
    <p>AllSafe IT maintains SOC 2 Type II certification and implements industry-standard security measures to protect client data. Both parties agree to maintain the confidentiality of proprietary information exchanged in connection with this Agreement.</p>
    <p>AllSafe IT will not disclose client data to third parties except as necessary to deliver the contracted services, as required by law, or as authorized in writing by the client.</p>

    <h2>V. Service Level Agreement (SLA)</h2>
    <p>AllSafe IT targets a 15-minute response time for critical issues and strives for 99.999% uptime across managed infrastructure. Specific SLA terms, including remedies for failure to meet targets, are detailed in the applicable Service Order.</p>
    <p>SLA credits, if applicable, represent the client's sole remedy for service level failures and shall not exceed the monthly fee for the affected service.</p>

    <h2>VI. Intellectual Property</h2>
    <p>Each party retains ownership of its pre-existing intellectual property. Any tools, methodologies, or software developed by AllSafe IT during the delivery of services remain the intellectual property of AllSafe IT unless expressly agreed otherwise in writing.</p>

    <h2>VII. Termination and Cancellation</h2>
    <p>Either party may terminate this Agreement with 30 days' written notice. AllSafe IT may terminate immediately upon material breach by the client, including non-payment. Upon termination, AllSafe IT will provide reasonable transition assistance and return client data in a mutually agreed format.</p>

    <h2>VIII. Liability and Indemnification</h2>
    <p>AllSafe IT's total liability under this Agreement shall not exceed the fees paid by the client in the three months preceding the claim. AllSafe IT is not liable for indirect, consequential, or punitive damages.</p>
    <p>Each party agrees to indemnify and hold harmless the other from claims arising from its own negligence, willful misconduct, or breach of this Agreement.</p>

    <h2>IX. Dispute Resolution</h2>
    <p>The parties agree to attempt to resolve disputes through good-faith negotiation. If negotiation fails, disputes shall be submitted to binding arbitration in Los Angeles County, California, under the rules of the American Arbitration Association.</p>

    <h2>X. Governing Law and Jurisdiction</h2>
    <p>This Agreement is governed by the laws of the State of California. Any legal proceedings not subject to arbitration shall be brought in the state or federal courts located in Los Angeles County, California.</p>

    <h2>XI. Miscellaneous</h2>
    <p>This Agreement constitutes the entire agreement between the parties with respect to its subject matter. If any provision is found unenforceable, the remaining provisions continue in full force. Failure to enforce any provision does not constitute a waiver. Neither party is liable for delays caused by circumstances beyond its reasonable control.</p>
